Package com.cafean.utils

Interface ChannelDataHolder

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    ConditionSet, PartialConditionSet, RestartData
    public interface ChannelDataHolder
    This interface indicates a data structure where components can obtain initial conditions data by plot-variable name.

      • getChannelDataValue

        default void getChannelDataValue​(java.lang.String dataName,
                                 CReal real,
                                 boolean preserveNumerics)
        This method sets the value of a provided CReal to the value with the given name. This uses the #getUnits() method above to ensure that the engineering units are correct.
        Parameters:
        dataName - the name of the data channel being read in.
        real - the CReal that is being set from the data channel.
        preserveNumerics - when TRUE this ensures that any reference to a numeric variable is preserved.

      • getChannelDataValue

        Parameters:

        integer - the CInteger that is being set from the data channel.
        preserveNumerics - when TRUE this ensures that any reference to a numeric variable is preserved.
